# PRIVACY POLICY FOR MINNEJAKT

Thank you for using Minnejakt (the "App"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and disclose information from and about users of our App. By using our App, you consent to the collection, use, and disclosure of your information as described in this Privacy Policy.

## Information We Collect

We do not collect any personal information from you as you use the App, such as your name, email address, or other personally identifiable information.

However, we use third-party services, such as Google Analytics, to collect information about how you use the App. This information may include your IP address, device type, browser type, operating system, the pages or features of the App that you use, the time and date of your visit, and other usage statistics. We use this information to improve the App and understand how users interact with it.

We may also display ads in the App, and our ad partners may collect certain information about your device and its usage in order to serve you more relevant ads. Please note that we do not control the data collection practices of our ad partners, and their privacy policies will govern their use of your information.

## Use of Information

We use the information we collect to provide and improve the App, and to analyze and understand how users interact with the App. We may use your information to personalize your experience and to deliver more relevant ads.

## Disclosure of Information

We may disclose the information we collect to third-party service providers that assist us in providing and improving the App, such as our analytics provider and our ad partners. These service providers may have access to your information only to perform services on our behalf and are obligated not to disclose or use it for any other purpose.

We may also disclose your information if required by law or if we believe that such disclosure is necessary to protect our rights and property or the safety of our users or the public.

## Third-Party Links

Our App may contain links to third-party websites or services that are not owned or controlled by us. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third-party websites or services. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of these websites or services before providing any personal information to them.

## Changes to Our Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or applicable laws. If we make material changes to this Privacy Policy, we will notify you by posting the updated Privacy Policy on our website or in the App, or by email or other means as required by law.
